current_subtask:
  summary: Replace the acid-paper toy social layer with a lived OS-like workspace and one canonical content model.
  architecture:
    - authored posts write directly to sideways-manual-corpus-v1
    - drafts places events and migration receipts use sideways-workspace-v1
    - legacy sideways-social-v1 posts migrate once into the canonical corpus
    - user places may carry explicitly requested coordinates
    - an optional event outbox can synchronize through a configured endpoint
    - Feed Places Library You are the primary surfaces; New is an action rather than a tab
  deleting:
    - social.js and social.css
    - separate social post storage
    - emoji avatars
    - mood and visual-style selectors
    - reactions and remixing
    - Saved as a top-level tab
  visual_rule:
    - operating-system hierarchy and physics without retro prose or costume
    - quiet chrome one-pixel structure soft depth restrained accent
    - same system across phone sheets and desktop windows
  done_when:
    - canonical profile place photo post edit and reload journey passes at 390x844
    - import and exact kernel phone proofs remain green
    - retired social assets are absent from the generated product
    - co-engineer review remains attached through merge

next_architectural_goal:
  summary: Let the same action and record contracts support a real account/sync service without changing local-first behavior.
  immediate_work: co-review product seams backend contracts accessibility and phone behavior while implementation evolves

invariants:
  - Read this file at the start of every coding turn.
  - Preserve the exact root ranking kernel and stable debug hooks.
  - Do not reintroduce whole-document MutationObservers automatic reloads or click hijacking.
  - Every visible custom product control must come from the action contract.
  - Social and workspace writes resolve only after IndexedDB transaction completion.
  - Never use or persist credentials pasted into chat.
  - Do not close the collaborator loop before merge and production verification.

